description: ======= ArmadaChartSpec Definition ======= ArmadaChartSpec defines the desired state of ArmadaChart

create.description: | pre         | object   | actions performed prior to updating a release                 |

reference.description: (optional) branch, commit, or reference in the repo (``master`` if not specified)

subpath.description: (optional) relative path to target chart from parent (``.`` if not specified)

location.description: ``url`` or ``path`` to the chart's parent directory

type.description: source to build the chart: ``git``, ``local``, or ``tar``

options.description: Test. JEB that structure could not be converted automatically

target_state.description: Target state of the Helm Custom Resources

continue_processing.description: do not delete FAILED releases when encountered from previous run (provide the 'continue_processing' bool to continue or halt execution (default: halt))

timeout.description: time (in seconds) allotted for chart to deploy when 'wait' flag is set (DEPRECATED)

release.description: name of the release (Armada will prepend with ``release-prefix`` during processing)

revisionHistoryLimit.description: revisionHistoryLimit is the maximum number of revisions that will be maintained in the ArmadaChart's revision history. The revision history consists of all revisions not represented by a currently applied ArmadaChartSpec version. The default value is 10.

labels.description: Base mapping of labels to wait on. They are added to any labels in each item in the ``resources`` array.

min_ready.description: Only for controller ``type``s. Amount of pods in a controller which must be ready. Can be integer or percent string e.g. ``80%``. Default ``100%``.

resources.description: Array of `Wait Resource`_ to wait on, with ``labels`` added to each item. Defaults to pods and jobs (if any exist) matching ``labels``.

timeout.description: time (in seconds) to wait for chart to deploy

enabled.description: Config for the native ``helm (install|upgrade) --wait`` flag. defaults to true

dependencies.description: reference any chart dependencies before install

timeout.description: time (in seconds) to wait for chart to be deleted
